{
  "texts": [
    "It is reasonable to expect that more AI-based tools will join the arsenal of the scientist.",
    "While caution (based, as ever, on the beneficence, autonomy, and fairness and the avoidance of maleficence principles) regarding the tools' creation, application and implications must be exercised, many of these tools will provide important and progressive support to scientific advancements 8, and should be embraced.",
    "Returning to LLM tools and how they can support the academic writing process, two inviolable principles merit further reflection: ownership and transparency.",
    "AI raises complex questions about these two principles; however, for the time being, the five-tier system, plus the appropriate use of supplementary material, may help to clarify questions around authorship, responsibility, and where we should stand on the place of the thinking process.",
    "ownership is the tenet that a submitted or published work and all of its contents remain the responsibility of a human author, and that the author is the only accountable party for mistakes or other consequences emanating from the work."
  ]
}